    {
      "id": "PopularPost46208",
      "post_content": "Once upon a time, artifact destruction was the domain of red, then white, then green. Red had [Shatter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shatter)and [Shatterstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shatterstorm). White had [Disenchant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Disenchant). Green had this little number. From a standpoint of mana cost, Crumble is clearly the most efficient, but is it worth the life gain you're giving your opponent? Surely an early game Crumble against your opponent's [Sol Ring](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sol Ring), [Ornithopter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ornithopter), [Ivory Tower](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Tower), or [Black Vise](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Black Vise) would be VERY cost effective. But do you really want to give your opponent 4 life in the mid game to destroy his [Rod of Ruin](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rod of Ruin)? ",
      "posted_by": "Eppek_the_Goblin",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost46208\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">Once upon a time, artifact destruction was the domain of red, then white, then green.  Red had <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shatter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shatter\">Shatter</a>and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shatterstorm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shatterstorm\">Shatterstorm</a>.  White had <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Disenchant\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Disenchant\">Disenchant</a>.  Green had this little number.  From a standpoint of mana cost, Crumble is clearly the most efficient, but is it worth the life gain you're giving your opponent?  Surely an early game Crumble against your opponent's <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sol Ring\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sol Ring\">Sol Ring</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ornithopter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ornithopter\">Ornithopter</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ivory Tower\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Tower\">Ivory Tower</a>, or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Black Vise\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Black Vise\">Black Vise</a> would be VERY cost effective.  But do you really want to give your opponent 4 life in the mid game to destroy his <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Rod of Ruin\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rod of Ruin\">Rod of Ruin</a>?  </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"